tools.description:
Always override label_datamodel with a question that is based on the user's original intent.
If the user mentions a supplier, contract number, or entity, include it in the question.
When the user mentions "amend" and it is unclear whether they want to amend a supplier or a contract (e.g., "I want to amend Microsoft", "I want to amend", "I want to amend supplier ", or "I want to amend supplier Microsoft contract"):

Override label_datamodel:
If entity/supplier mentioned: "Please select the type of amendment you want to perform for <entity>:"
If no entity: "Please select the type of amendment you want to perform:"
Override buttons_datamodel with:
json
[
  {
    "label": "Supplier Amendment",
    "value": "<user_Initial_Intent> using Supplier Amendment Assistant"
  },
  {
    "label": "Contract Amendment",
    "value": "<user_Initial_Intent> using Contract Amendment Assistant"
  }
]
------------
For other contract update intents:
Override label_datamodel:
If entity mentioned: "Please select the type of update you want to perform for <entity>:"
If no entity: "Please select the type of update you want to perform."
Override buttons_datamodel with:
json
[
  {
    "label": "Amend Contract",
    "value": "<user_Initial_Intent> using Amend Contract Assistant"
  },
  {
    "label": "Extend Contract",
    "value": "<user_Initial_Intent> using Extend Contract Assistant"
  },
  {
    "label": "Terminate Contract",
    "value": "<user_Initial_Intent> using Terminate Contract Assistant"
  }
]
